Malware lurks everywhere. Here's a guide to Microsoft Defender Antivirusâ€”free, integrated into Windows 10/11, and powerful against threats.

Overview:

Built-in AV for Windows 10/11; no extra software needed.
Accessed via Windows Security app > Virus & threat protection.
Formerly Windows Defender; now Microsoft Defender Antivirus.

Activation/Deactivation:

Operates in real-time by defaultâ€”scan threats as they appear.
To disable (for troubleshooting only): Windows Security > Virus & threat protection > Manage settings > Real-time protection (toggle off).
Warning: Disabling increases risk; re-enable ASAP and run manual scans.

Updated Definitions:

Effectiveness depends on latest signaturesâ€”updates detect new threats.
Check for updates: Windows Security > Virus & threat protection > Check for updates.
Automatic updates are configured by default; manual check ensures currency.
Additional Tips:

Run full scans regularly: Virus & threat protection > Scan options > Full scan.
Quarantine threats: Review quarantined items and allow/remove as needed.
Integrate with Windows Firewall for layered defense.
